parameters:
Knight: The hall is off-limits. I
apologize.

Knight: I have received permission from
Lady Mel. Please come in.

Zerachiel: I can't believe I'm allowed
to enter the Throne Room...

Lala: And it's the Demon Lord's castle
too?

Claudia: It's quite interesting that
angels are in the Demon Continent, isn't
it?

Knight: If you're looking for the Demon
Lord, she's in the back.

The knight: It seems that when Mel-sama
was young, her mother passed away, and
she often clashed with the Demon Lord.

Knight: And so, when she was 16 years
old, she left the Demon Continent and
became an adventurer in the Imperial
Territory.

Knight: It seems that she reconciled
with the Demon Lord through letters.

Knight: If Lady Mel hasn't returned, I
wonder what has become of Vaal by now...

Knight: As a knight, I intend to
dedicate my life to Lady Mel.

Claudia: In the recent attack, the
knights who didn't run away, stood their
ground, and fought until the end while
helping the injured...

Claudia: Seeing that noble figure, I
wonder if trust was born.

Lala: If there's a king like Sariel, I
would run away immediately...

Lala: I think I would fight until the
end for Mel's sake.

Knight: If it's Zerachiel-sama, you're
welcome anytime.
Knight: Please take your time and relax.

Knight: Lady Sachia, thank you for
taking care of the sword earlier.

Knight: Thanks to you, it has excellent
sharpness.

Sachia: Ahaha, if I could be of help,
then that's the best thing.

Zerachiel: You came to play, yet you
sharpened the sword for me?

Sachia: Yeah, because the blade was all
worn out.

Sachia: I've been familiar with handling
blades since I was young, so I enjoy
sharpening them.

Knight: Lady Rabi! Thank you for the
martial arts training!
Rabi: Oh no, it was fun!

Rabi: Since I enjoy training, please
feel free to call on me anytime.
Knight: Yes! I'm counting on you!

Knight: Lady Mel and the others are not
here.

Knight: They have set out to defeat the
monsters in the underground volcano.

Zerachiel: So everyone was fighting for
me, huh.

Lala: I've been wanting to meet your
friends.

Knight: Lady Claudia! Please refrain
from drinking alcohol!

Knight: I heard that it was tough for
the maids!
Claudia: I heard it from Rabi, but...

Claudia: It seems that I, who was drunk,
took off my clothes and cast magic
spells one after another while naked.

Claudia: I... I like alcohol. Please
don't look at me with pity.

Knight: Please leave the defense of the
castle to us.
Azel: Yes, please leave it to us.

Knight: Zerachiel-san! You are truly
worthy of being a knight! Thank you very
much!

Zerachiel: I'm so carefree, so being a
knight might not suit me.

Effy: It seems impossible for me too. I
want to go back to a life where I am
taken care of...

Knight: It seems that Lady Unie and Lord
Ishvald were mercenaries.

Knight: It seems they have known each
other since they were young.

Knight: In the Cave of Blazing Sands,
there is a nest generated around a
goblin named Oldelic, who is cunning and
full of mischief.

Knight: There are many goblins. Please
be careful.

Sachia: That's useful information. Thank
you for telling me.

Knight: It seems that Lady Unie and Lord
Ishvald were mercenaries.

Knight: It seems they have known each
other since they were young.

Knight: We have information that Lamias
inhabit the Magic Ore Mountain.

Knight: Be careful as Lamias have poison
that can cause you to fall into a coma
and enter a sleep state when attacked.

Knight: It seems that Lady Unie and Lord
Ishvald were mercenaries.

Knight: It seems they have known each
other since they were young.

Knight: Due to the commotion in the
underground volcano, most of the knights
are absent.
Knight: We are on duty... sigh...

Zerachiel: It's an important job to
protect the fort while everyone is away.

Lala: Hehe, it's proof that I'm trusted,
isn't it?

Knight: One of the reasons why the
Starry Forest was closed is because
women are being attacked one after
another.

Knight: It seems that a strange monster
girl is attacking only women. Please be
careful.

Zerachiel: Oh, I wonder what kind of
monster it is?

Claudia: Let's pray that we don't
encounter it.

Knight: It seems that the Demon Lord has
returned, according to rumors.

Knight: If we have the Demon Lord, the
Demon Continent will be fine.

Zerachiel: The Demon Lord, is he really
that amazing...

Azel: Yes, that's true. While he may be
a bold person, there are very few who
can defeat the Demon Lord, I suppose.

Azel: Um, about the former wife... Queen
Ruberie-sama was there...

Azel: There was a time when the Demon
Lord's infidelity was discovered, and we
had a fight.

Azel: At that time, seven islands were
blown away, and the Demon Lord suffered
a serious injury, while the Queen was
unharmed.
Lala: What's that? It's not a monster...

Knight: Is that the Holy Maiden over
there!? S-She's so beautiful...
Effy: Oh, thank you very much.

Zerachiel: Be careful, Effy. It seems
she has sprouted.

Effy: You don't have to say unnecessary
things, you know.

Claudia: I'll help with the creation of
the antidote as well.

Claudia: I have knowledge of potion-
making, so leave it to me.
Zerachiel: I'm counting on you, Claudia.

Sachia: Ahaha, I'm not good at cooking
though.

Sachia: No, I didn't say anything!
Ahaha...

Zerachiel: (These two get along well,
don't they?)

Claudia: The \c[6]Earth's Jewel\c[0] is
considered a sacred relic.

Claudia: It is imbued with the magic of
the gods.

Claudia: It seems that they sealed it in
a desert ruin because its power is too
immense.

Zerachiel: But it seems like the goblins
had taken it.

Claudia: ...It seems like too much time
has passed, and even the Demon Lord has
forgotten about its existence.
Zerachiel: You found it quite well...

Claudia: As expected of the demon
castle. There are so many valuable
documents here.

Claudia: It's no wonder that Mel is so
knowledgeable.

Rabi: I'm happy to be surrounded by
grimoires.

Rabi: I'm definitely pulling an all-
nighter.

Claudia: It seems that there is a
volcanic city where people can live
underground in the Demon Continent.
Claudia: I want to go too...

Zerachiel: I wonder if she's jealous.
She's glaring at me with a sharp gaze...
Sachia: Good work, both of you.

Sachia: The incident at the underground
volcano was tough, but I'm glad we were
able to resolve it safely.
Zerachiel: Thanks to you, I was saved.

Sachia: I'll go ahead and prepare the
curse-breaking medicine, so please do
your best to gather the \c[6]resin
gemstones\c[0].

Knight: There aren't many demons like
me, but it's rare to find a child like
you who isn't surprised.

Knight: There aren't many demons like
me, but it's rare to find a child like
you who isn't surprised.

Knight: I deeply appreciate that you
helped Lady Mel.

Knight: However, you are also angels. If
they don't know the circumstances, there
may be those who are cautious.

Zerachiel: Don't worry, I'm not bothered
by it.

Lala: That's right! You don't have to
worry about it!!

Lala: In the past, I was sold off to a
freak show just because I was a rare
angel, but this is way better than
that!!

Claudia: Y-You're going through a lot of
hardships, aren't you...

Azel: I understand how you feel, Lala-
san...

Azel: I, too, in the past, as part of my
training under my master, was sold to
slave traders...

Zerachiel: What kind of life are you all
living?

Claudia: (I can't really say anything
about others either.)

Knight: The spirits are watching over
you. Keep doing your best from now on.

Zerachiel: I wonder what form the
spirits take?

Effy: Most of them are cute spirits, but
it seems there are also strong spirits.

Effy: Yes, there are already various
things...

Knight: I also have demon blood, but I
look normal, right?

Knight: It seems like the demon race is
becoming diluted because their
reproductive ability is low.

Knight: I also have demon blood, but I
look normal, right?

Knight: It seems like the demon race is
becoming diluted because their
reproductive ability is low.

Knight: I somehow managed to survive...
thanks to all of you.

Knight: I will express my gratitude,
thank you.

Zerachiel: Oh, there's no need for
thanks...

Lala: I think there are very few angels
recognized by the demons.
Zerachiel: Ehehe, I'm glad you're safe.

Knight: True courage possesses the power
to overcome any obstacle. I have read
about it in ancient documents.

Zerachiel: It's always nice to be
praised, isn't it?

Effy: It's okay to get carried away for
now.

Maid: Since there are few maids,
cleaning is quite difficult...

Maid: The vase was broken... I wonder
who the culprit is...

Rabi: W-Who could it be! I won't forgive
them!

Maid: Since the castle knights are
currently away, let's clean the areas
that we usually can't clean.

Lala: You can even snoop around in
private.

Maid: Since there are few maids,
cleaning is quite difficult...

Zerachiel: Maybe because it's a small
castle?

Claudia: That might be true, but it
could also be about wanting to work in
the Demon Lord's castle for the cleaning
job.
Claudia: Normally, I would be scared.

Maid: The damage to the town was beyond
comparison to that of the castle. I also
lost a friend.

Maid: ...If I hadn't been in the castle,
would I have died too?

Maid: Everyone, please make sure to come
back.

Maid: Ah, thank goodness! Everyone is
safe...

Zerachiel: It seems like you were really
worried.
Effy: Hehe, I can feel your relief.

Maid: I have to clean the floor by
today. Every single day... it's tough.

Maid: It's been a while since I've been
in such a quiet castle.
Zerachiel: It's almost empty, isn't it?

Lala: Now I can sing without being
heard, right?

Maid: Now that the knights have
returned, cleaning has become difficult
again.

Maid: This side has more excitement,
doesn't it?

Zerachiel: Even though it seemed so
difficult...

Claudia: I'm sure you must love this
job.

Maid: Even someone like me should be
able to do something.

Maid: The castle needs to be cleaned
again, doesn't it?

Maid: There are many injured people, so
it's tough, but I will do my best until
the end!!

Zerachiel: Even though she hated it so
much...

Claudia: That girl is also fighting.
Within her own capabilities, of course.

Maid: In order to greet everyone with a
smile when you all come back, I will do
my best at cleaning.

Maid: You finally did it! The knights
have returned too!!

Zerachiel: It's great to see you so
happy.
Effy: I'm sure you were worried.

Rabi: I have been tasked with gathering
other materials in the underground
warehouse.
Rabi: I wanted to go too...

Sachia: When I come back from the
desert, I'll change for you.

Zerachiel: Please take care of it then,
Rabi.
Rabi: Tomorrow, I will accompany you.

Rabi: I'll go pick you up at the inn, so
you should take it easy and rest today.

Zerachiel: I'll take you up on your
offer. See you tomorrow.

Rabi: It was fun going to the mine
together. I'll rely on you again, okay?
Zerachiel: Nice to meet you too.

Rabi: I fought against monsters during
the underground volcano incident...
Rabi: It was fun to move my body a lot!

Claudia: Fufu, Rabi, you haven't changed
a bit.

Rabi: Are we going to the Starry Forest?
Be careful, okay.

Unie: I'm collecting materials on
curses! There's so much of it, it's
tough!

Unie: I'll do my best to make the
antidote right away!
Zerachiel: Let's both do our best, okay.

Unie: The underground city is so hot,
you know~. Be careful not to slip and
fall into the lava, okay?

Zerachiel: It seems like there won't
even be any bones left at that time.

Unie: The commotion in the underground
volcano is over, and I've almost
gathered all the materials for the
curse-breaking potion~!

Zerachiel: I'll go find the final
ingredient.

Mel: I'll gather other materials just in
case. Be careful, okay?

Zerachiel: It's okay because Sachia is
here.

Sachia: I'll do my best not to
disappoint your expectations.

Mel: I've rented a place to stay. It
would be good for you to rest and relax
there.

Mel: I heard that there are many
tentacles in the magic ore mine.
Mel: Both of you, be careful.

Rabi: Hehe, I'm confident because I have
plenty of experience! My training
methods are different from yours, after
all!

Mel: Zerachiel, if things get dangerous,
it would be good to use Rabi as a decoy.

Rabi: I apologize for getting carried
away.

Zerachiel: Ahaha, you two get along
well.

Mel: The underground city is located
between this city and the port town. I'm
counting on you.

Zerachiel: Understood, I'll go check it
out.
Mel: Zerachiel, Claudia. Don't push yourself too hard, okay.

Claudia: I'll hurry and gather the
\c[6]resin gems\c[0].

Zerachiel: I'm going to the Forest of
Star Divination.

Sachia: Tomorrow will be tough too, so
make sure to rest and relax a bit.
Sachia: Good morning, both of you.

Sachia: Since tomorrow will be tough
too, make sure to rest and relax a bit.
Sachia: You're going to the Magic Ore Mine today, right? Be careful, okay.
Sachia: Here, I'll give this to you.
Zerachiel: Thank you, I'll treasure it.

Sachia: Ahaha, I'll be in trouble if you
don't use it.
Sachia: Both of you, do your best.
Rabi: I'll be off right away!

Sachia: I wonder what kind of person the
captain is.

Zerachiel: I hope he's not a scary
person.
